&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Senior Infrastructure Engineer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 - Full Time (37.5 hours) - Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Surrey County NHS Foundation Trust and are seeking to recruit an experienced Senior Infrastructure Engineer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Infrastructure Engineer supports the IT Infrastructure Operations Manager who is responsible for the administration and optimisation of the organisation’s IT data centre, network, client devices and associated components to achieve high performance and availability of a range of business applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior IT Infrastructure Engineers are responsible for ensuring the availability of selected client/server applications, networks, firewalls, and client devices, configuring all new implementations and developing processes and procedures for the ongoing management of the technology estate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role calls for someone to be a highly specialist resource within IT and as such will have, or will develop, technical or specialist excellence across the range of technologies and services that fall under the responsibility of the infrastructure team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will often have opportunities to work on project work and the adoption of new technologies in line with business requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The IT team currently operates core-hours between 8.00am to 5.00pm, Monday to Friday, and the successful candidate will have a flexible attitude to be able to adjust to the operational needs of the department as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to talk to somebody about this vacancy then please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adrian Burnett&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Head of IT Business Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Royal Surrey County Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Egerton Road, Guildford, Surrey, GU2 7XX&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: adrian.burnett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
